message.content: One of the most significant events that occurred in Tonga in the past five years was the coronation of King Tupou VI on July 4, 2015. This event marked the official ascension of King Tupou VI to the throne following the death of his brother, King George Tupou V, in 2012. The coronation ceremony was a grand and elaborate affair, attended by dignitaries from around the world, and it symbolized the continuity of Tonga's monarchy and the country's commitment to its traditional values and cultural heritage.
